article.headline: E. Washington 41, UC Davis 31
article.story: CHENEY, Wash. (AP) -- Matt Nichols threw for 252 yards and two touchdowns as Eastern Washington beat UC Davis 41-31 in a non-conference game Saturday that saw the teams roll up nearly 1,000 yards of offense. Nichols completed 25 of 42 passes and Dale Morris had three rushing touchdowns to help the Eagles (2-0) outlast the Aggies (1-2). The teams combined for 995 yards -- including 517 by UC Davis -- and 102 pass attempts. With EWU ahead 34-24 midway through the fourth quarter and UC Davis driving, the Eagles' Lonnie Hosley intercepted a Tim Plough pass at the goal line. The next two plays -- runs of 50 yards by Alexis Alexander and 33 yards by Morris -- pushed the ball deep into UC Davis territory before Morris carried it in from the 3-yard line to give the Eagles a 41-24 advantage. Nichols' 32-yard scoring strike to Brynsen Brown had given Eastern a 27-17 lead with 4:23 left in the third quarter. The Aggies answered on Kale Turner's 25-yard TD reception from Plough to pull within 27-24 early in the fourth. Nichols' 6-yard scoring toss Tom McAndrews then pushed the EWU lead to 34-24 with 9:57 left in the game. Turner, who had eight catches for 107 yards, also had an 88-yard scoring run in the first half. Plough finished 38 of 58 for 388 yards, with two TDs and two interceptions. For Eastern, Alexander finished with 122 yards and a touchdown on 17 carries, and Aaron Boyce had nine catches for 107 yards, all in the first half.
